elements.title: Daisy (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Monique Corzilius did not realize that she was the girl featured in the famous "Daisy" advertisement (pictured) until the 2000s, when she searched for the commercial on the Internet?

elements.title: William Rundell (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Victorian post office official William Rundell also collected stamps in his spare time, acquiring 48 copies of the "Sydney view" stamps of New South Wales?

elements.title: rare skipper (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the butterfly rare skipper was only known from five rivers in the United States until sometime in the 1980s?

elements.title: John Henry Dunn (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that John Henry Dunn resigned from the Executive Council of Upper Canada only three weeks after his appointment, throwing away a post he had sought for 16 years, on a matter of political principle?

elements.title: Lyduvėnai (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the Lithuanian town of Lyduvėnai had one of the world's largest wooden bridges?

elements.title: Erawan Hotel (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the construction of the Erawan Hotel was delayed by so many mishaps that a shrine to Brahma was built to ward off ill fortune?

elements.title: Hakan Akkaya (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Hakan Akkaya became Turkey's first wheelchair fencer in 2013?

elements.title: Green Guerillas (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the Green Guerillas threw "seed grenades" into abandoned lots in New York City?
